                    "description": "Intervict is a research institute that is dedicated to reseach on victims of crime and abuse of power. The two main projects I worked on at Intervict were the ICVS and Evaluation of the EU crime survey. The ICVS is a standardised survey on victimisation by crime, crime prevention and policing. My responsibility was the management of the main datafile, data analysis and drafting the main reports that were published in 2006 and 2007. Furthermore I was part of the team that evaluated the pilot studies on a EU victimisation survey project that is scheduled to be done on a regular basis in the near future. The report finalised in 2010.\n\nHe is currently affiliated with the DSP-groep in Amsterdam. This is an organisation specialised in policy oriented research.  In the mean time he is also working on a number of publications that will lead to a Ph.D. at Tilburg University.",
